ContainerType.Name: AQ_DocumentLink
ContainerType.Description: Generic container to display a link to a document

Parameter.Name: asset-name
Parameter.Description: Refers to an asset used to display the link text

Parameter.Name: asset-type
Parameter.Description: Refers to an asset format used to display the link text

Parameter.Name: document-name
Parameter.Description: Expression that refers to the document that should be rendered, string values must be between quotes (eg: "simpledocument")

Parameter.Name: document-type
Parameter.Description: Expression that defines the document type, string values must be between quotes (eg: "pdf")

Parameter.Name: optional-parameters
Parameter.Description: Optional expression that are appended to the link, string values must be between quotes

ContentStyle.Name: AddressLine
ContentStyle.Description: One line in an address block

ContentStyle.Name: EmptyLine
ContentStyle.Description: An empty vertical space with the height of a text line

ContentStyle.Name: Header
ContentStyle.Description: Text that is shown at the top of every page, except the first page. Used for page title, etc.

ContentStyle.Name: Body
ContentStyle.Description: The main content of a document, i.e., excluding page title, TOC, index, etc.

ContentStyle.Name: AddressBlock
ContentStyle.Description: Paragraph of address lines, e.g., for a letter. Has a fixed place on the page, should be placed in Header or HeaderFirst.

ContentStyle.Name: TableCell
ContentStyle.Description: Table cell. Should be inserted in a table line.

ContentStyle.Name: TableRow
ContentStyle.Description: One row in a table, containing "normal" contents, i.e., not column headings or summations

ContentStyle.Name: HeaderFirst
ContentStyle.Description: Text that is shown at the top of the first page. If no content item with HeaderFirst is present, the Header content item is used.

ContentStyle.Name: TableOfContents
ContentStyle.Description: Content style that expands into a table of contents

ContentStyle.Name: List
ContentStyle.Description: An enumerated or bulleted list

ContentStyle.Name: AttributeList
ContentStyle.Description: A list of attribute-value pairs. Has a fixed place on the page, should be placed in Header or HeaderFirst.

ContentStyle.Name: HorizontalLine
ContentStyle.Description: Horizontal line over the full width of the containing element

ContentStyle.Name: TableHeader
ContentStyle.Description: The top line of a table, used for column headings etc.

ContentStyle.Name: Footer
ContentStyle.Description: Text that is shown at the bottom of every page, except the first page. Used for page numbers etc.

ContentStyle.Name: KeepTogether
ContentStyle.Description: Attempt to keep child content items together on one page

ContentStyle.Name: FooterFirst
ContentStyle.Description: Text that is shown at the bottom of the first page. If no content item with FooterFirst is present, the Footer content item is used.

ContentStyle.Name: TableFooter
ContentStyle.Description: The bottom line of a table, used for summations etc.

ContentStyle.Name: Colophon
ContentStyle.Description: Text that describes meta information about a document, e.g., author, version, publishing information. Has a fixed place on the page, should be placed in Header or HeaderFirst.

ContentStyle.Name: Heading1
ContentStyle.Description: Highest level of hierarchical paragraphs. Contains Heading1Title for the actual title, and also the text of the paragraphs

ContentStyle.Name: ListClosingSign
ContentStyle.Description: An enumerated or bulleted list. Closes every item with a semicolon ';', and the last item with a period '.'

ContentStyle.Name: PageBreak
ContentStyle.Description: Setting this content style forces a page break

ContentStyle.Name: DocumentTitle
ContentStyle.Description: Title of the document. Has a fixed place on the page, should be placed in Header or HeaderFirst.

ContentStyle.Name: ListElement
ContentStyle.Description: One item in an enumerated or bulleted list

ContentStyle.Name: TableOfContents_Footer
ContentStyle.Description: Text that is shown at the bottom of page showing the table of contents.

ContentStyle.Name: Attribute
ContentStyle.Description: One attribute-value pair (attribute title and attribute value). Should be placed in Attributes

ContentStyle.Name: Columns
ContentStyle.Description: Formats the contained content item into one column on a page

ContentStyle.Name: Heading2
ContentStyle.Description: Second level of hierarchical paragraphs. Contains Heading2Title for the actual title, and also the text of the paragraphs

ContentStyle.Name: Heading1Title
ContentStyle.Description: The title of a heading 1

ContentStyle.Name: PageNumber
ContentStyle.Description: Inserts a page number

ContentStyle.Name: ColophonLine
ContentStyle.Description: A line in a colophon

ContentStyle.Name: TableOfContents_Header
ContentStyle.Description: Header for the page showing the table of contents

ContentStyle.Name: Heading2Title
ContentStyle.Description: The title of a heading 2

ContentStyle.Name: Heading3
ContentStyle.Description: Third level of hierarchical paragraphs. Contains Heading3Title for the actual title, and also the text of the paragraphs

ContentStyle.Name: AttributeValue
ContentStyle.Description: The value part of an attribute value pair. Should be placed in Attribute.

ContentStyle.Name: AttributeTitle
ContentStyle.Description: The title part of an attribute-value pair. Should be placed in Attribute

ContentStyle.Name: Heading3Title
ContentStyle.Description: The title of a heading 3

ContentStyle.Name: Heading4
ContentStyle.Description: Fourth level of hierarchical paragraphs. Contains Heading4Title for the actual title, and also the text of the paragraphs

ContentStyle.Name: Heading4Title
ContentStyle.Description: The title of a heading 4

ContentStyle.Name: Heading5
ContentStyle.Description: Fifth level of hierarchical paragraphs. Contains Heading5Title for the actual title, and also the text of the paragraphs

ContentStyle.Name: Heading5Title
ContentStyle.Description: The title of a heading 5

MaskType.Name: AQ_NumberPattern
MaskType.Description: This masktype is used to display numbers. Check the Aquima helpfiles for a complete description of the patterns to use in this masktype.

Parameter.Name: pattern
Parameter.Description: Most common options: # - indicates an optional position, 0 - indicates a required position, use dot's or comma's as separators.

Parameter.Name: prefix
Parameter.Description: String value: string displayed in front of the number value

Parameter.Name: postfix
Parameter.Description: String value: string displayed after the number value

Parameter.Name: zero-fraction
Parameter.Description: String value that substitutes the fraction part when the fraction is zero. For instance to replace ,00 with ,-

Node.Content: Undersigned declares to agree with application of the General Terms. The General Terms are available for the public at the premises of the insurance company. Upon request this General Terms can be provided prior to signed of the insurance application form, or finally with the delivery of the insurance policy.
